results.overview:
Magnet schools are public school options that provide a school-wide curriculum designed around a specific theme. They are intended to attract a diverse pool of applicants and historically have accommodated students from outside their zone or district. While some schools may have the word "magnet" in their school's name, only a school that currently gets Magnet Schools Assistance Program (M.S.A.P) funding is labeled as a "magnet school" on it's MySchools page. This magnet school offers a school-wide curriculum around the theme of Art and Science. Our mission at P.S. 245 is to provide each student with engaging learning experiences and a rigorous educational program. Our goal is to empower each student to grow intellectually and socially and to ensure that each student graduates on a pathway to a rewarding career, long-term economic security and equipped to be a positive force for change			

Due to our unique small school size, it allows us to know each child closely. Students are provided with a nurturing academic and safe learning environment. Small group instruction takes place in every classroom, every day. During this time. students are provided with tailored differentiated instruction to meet their individual needs. 

Our school has a full-time guidance counselor and social worker who works in collaboration with classroom teachers to provide a supportive school community for all of our students. Each student will participate in PE, art and music classes throughout the year as well several school-wide events such as our Thanksgiving Feast, Holiday shows &Spring Fling.

results.overview:
PS 256 was built in 1959, and has always been an active participant in the Bedford-Stuyvesant community. Our school is named after Benjamin Banneker, a Black astronomer, naturalist, surveyor, and almanac author.  Directly across from the school lies the Hattie Carthan Community Garden. Facing the school, on its north side, is the Marcy Pool. About a half block east lie the Magnolia Tree Earth Center and Von King Park. These landmarks exemplify Bed-Stuyâs long-standing sense of community activism, self-determination and pride that are still prevalent today, even as the neighborhood experiences a demographic and economic shift. At PS 256, we embrace this thriving culture and are a part of it ourselves.

We are a non-zoned, public New York City Magnet School. Magnet schools are part of a select network of schools that offer innovative theme-based programs. As a Magnet school, we incorporate our theme of architecture and engineering into  our  interdisciplinary units of study rooted in Science & Social Studies concepts.

For Reading & Writing, we use EL Education, a content-based curriculum organized around themes. Students build background knowledge by reading about a range of topics. They then use that knowledge to build writing skills across the genres. In addition, we use the Eureka Math Curriculum, Amplify Science and Passport to Social Studies. 


Our school's core values are equity, joy, collaboration and community.  These values are woven throughout the curriculum and show up in our approach to teaching and learning.

results.overview:
At PS 262, we are dedicated to providing a nurturing and engaging learning environment for our youngest learners. Our kindergarten program focuses on developing the whole child - academically, socially, and emotionally - ensuring a strong foundation for lifelong learning. Our mission is to inspire curiosity, creativity, and a love of learning in each child while fostering respect, kindness, and collaboration. Our science of reading curriculum includes the following elements:
Phonemic awareness: Isolating and working with spoken sounds.
Phonics instruction: Teaching how to read and spell words.
Content knowledge, vocabulary, and comprehension.
Heart word practice: Introducing or practicing new sight words.
Decoding and blending practice.
Decodable readers.
Guided writing.
We believe parents are our partners in education, and we work closely with families to support each child' development.
